      "id": "625de91c_3a823f80",
      "file_path": "integration-tests/pom.xml",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 54,
      "message": "Using the profile allows us to perform different test cases on the SDC environments (one with helm validator and one without), which in turn allows us to show that everything is still working as expected with or without the helm validator container (which was supposed to be optional).\n\nThere may be test cases then that would pass when container is disabled and fail when it's enabled and vice versa. I'm not sure how that should be controlled in the tests, unless we'd wan't to skip the tests without helm validator.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6044,
        "name": "Remigiusz Janeczek",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "remigiusz.janeczek@nokia.com",
        "username": "rjanecze"
      },
      "updated": "2021-05-26 13:28:14.000000000",
